doc.after: Although many species of Psittacosaurus have been named, their relationships to each other have not yet been fully explored and no scientific consensus exists on the subject.[4][41][44] Several phylogenetic analyses have been published, with the most detailed being those by Alexander Averianov and colleagues in 2006,[8] Hai-Lu You and colleagues in 2008,[40] and Paul Sereno in 2010.[36] The middle one is shown below.
